notes:
Dimensione has an Open Peering Policy, however we do have several basic requirements:

- We require peers to have and maintain a PeeringDB record;
- Peering partners must maintain a 24x7 NOC;
- Peering partners must cooperate in the troubleshooting of any peering related issues, denial of service attacks, and similar incidents;
- Peers must not abuse the peering relationship by doing any of the following non exhaustive list: pointing default, resetting next hop, selling or giving next hop to others, sending prefixes longer than /24, and so forth.

We reserve the right to temporarily suspend peering if it is determined to be causing harm to the Dimensione network. Peering may resume once the problem is resolved.
